<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
This species belongs to the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">miniatus</emphasis>
species group (
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. creticus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="creticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. creticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. haladai" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="haladai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. haladai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. larochei" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="larochei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. larochei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1992, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. marginatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hagens, 1882, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. miniatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="miniatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. miniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hagens, 1882, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. nomioidis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="nomioidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. nomioidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pesenko, 1979, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. schawrzi" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="schawrzi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. schawrzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Astafurova &amp; Proshchalykin, 2014, and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. sandykachis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="sandykachis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. sandykachis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Astafurova &amp; Proshchalykin, 2018), with the same length and transverse F1-F3 in females. Among species of this group 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. marginatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most close to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. miniatus" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="miniatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. miniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. nomioidis" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="nomioidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="24">S. nomioidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as they have a similar sculpture and structure of the body. Hence females of the three species are challenging to distinguish, but the male differs from the other two species by smaller triangular gonostylus. Differences between these three species are outlined by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3311.1.1" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B20" refString="Bogusch, P, Straka, J, 2012. Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). . Zootaxa 3311: 1 - 41" title="Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3311.1.1" volume="3311" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka (2012)</bibRefCitation>
and between females of this species group by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4441.1.4" author="Astafurova, YuV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" pagination="76 - 88" refId="B16" refString="Astafurova, YuV, Proshchalykin, MYu, Schwarz, M, 2018c. New and little known bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae) from Central Asia. . Zootaxa 4441: 76 - 88" title="New and little known bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille, 1804 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae) from Central Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4441.1.4" volume="4441" year="2018 c">Astafurova et al. (2018c)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
